underlying_goal: To commit recent work into the git repository.
primary_success: Claude correctly identified that the changed files represented two logically separate pieces of work and split them into two distinct, well-messaged commits.
brief_summary: The user requested to commit recent changes. Claude analyzed the modified files, identified that a recompiled PDF and a new specification feedback file were unrelated, and correctly created two separate commits with clear messages. It also warned the user about pushing directly to the main branch.
